On Sun, 22 Sep 2002 Bookwus1(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> Of the four warning lights only the highbeam indicator had (what appeared to
> be) a "blinder" in it.  This small piece of black plastic fit in the
> indicator light opening perfectly and had a small hole in the center.  The
> net effect was that, when the high beams were on, the "blinder" would allow
> only a small circle of light to show on the blue lens.

The other lights have to be seen in daylight and are normally out.  You
want to know _right away_ if they come on.  The highbeam indicator is
only used at night and you don't want it glaring brightly at the driver.

